# Intake And Planning

- Normalize every non-trivial request into a task packet with goal, constraints, files, durable choices, acceptance checks, and open questions.
- For multi-step work, keep the packet explicit and update it when the direction changes.
- Use `tools/agent/intake.sh` when you want the active task packet persisted into local session memory.
- Plan before editing when the task touches multiple files, architectural choices, or external behavior.
- Break execution into small verifiable steps and revisit the packet before delegating.
